---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionContainer from '../components/SectionContainer.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { clinic } from '../lib/site';

const lastUpdated = '2026-04-30';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${clinic.brandName} collects, uses, and protects information from website visitors. Read our privacy policy.`}
>
  <SectionContainer width="prose" spacing="md" background="paper-soft">
    <Breadcrumbs trail={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated"><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>
  </SectionContainer>

  <SectionContainer width="prose" spacing="lg">
    <p>
      {clinic.brandName} ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes
      how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit
      <a href="https://www.thewellnesswaymason.com">www.thewellnesswaymason.com</a> (the "Site").
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Important:</strong> protected health information (PHI) collected during your in-clinic
      patient relationship is governed by our HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices, provided to you at
      the time of your first visit and available upon request. This Privacy Policy applies only to
      information collected through this website.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information we collect on this website</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Information you give us voluntarily.</strong> When you submit our contact form, we
        collect your name, email address, phone number (if provided), and the content of your message.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Automatically collected technical data.</strong> Standard server logs and analytics
        may capture your IP address, device type, browser, pages visited, and referrer URL.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Cookies and similar technologies.</strong> Our website may use cookies to remember
        preferences and to support analytics tools (such as Google Analytics). You can disable cookies
        in your browser settings.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use website-collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respond to inquiries you submit through the Site;</li>
      <li>Schedule appointments or communicate about your interest in our services;</li>
      <li>Improve the Site, monitor traffic patterns, and understand which content is helpful;</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>We do not sell your information</strong> to third parties for advertising purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Information you should not submit through this website</h2>
    <p>
      To protect your privacy, please do not submit medical history, lab results, diagnoses,
      prescription information, or other Protected Health Information (PHI) through the contact form
      on this website. New patient intake is handled separately through our secure online booking
      system at <a href={clinic.bookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">our scheduling portal</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Third-party services</h2>
    <p>This Site may use third-party services to support its operation:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> hosts the website and processes server-side traffic logs.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Google Maps</strong> embed displays our clinic location.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Online appointment scheduling</strong> redirects to our third-party scheduling provider
        (Neo Platform) for new patient registration.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Web analytics</strong> tools (such as Google Analytics) may be used to understand
        aggregate site usage. These tools collect anonymized usage data.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each third-party service has its own privacy policy. We do not control how those services
      handle data once you interact with them directly.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      Contact form submissions are kept only as long as necessary to respond to your inquiry and
      to maintain a record of communications, then securely deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your choices</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Request a copy of any personal information we hold about you;</li>
      <li>Ask us to correct inaccurate information;</li>
      <li>Ask us to delete personal information we hold about you (subject to legal obligations);</li>
      <li>Opt out of analytics by disabling cookies in your browser or using browser-level Do Not Track signals.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
      <a href={`mailto:${clinic.email}`}>{clinic.email}</a> or call <a href={`tel:${clinic.phoneTel}`}>{clinic.phone}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our website is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from
      children under 13 through this website.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of
      this page reflects the most recent revision. Material changes will be reflected here.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this Privacy Policy or your information:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>{clinic.brandName}</strong><br />
      {clinic.address.streetAddress}<br />
      {clinic.address.addressLocality}, {clinic.address.addressRegion} {clinic.address.postalCode}<br />
      <a href={`tel:${clinic.phoneTel}`}>{clinic.phone}</a><br />
      <a href={`mailto:${clinic.email}`}>{clinic.email}</a>
    </p>

    <hr />

    <p class="disclaimer">
      <em>
        This Privacy Policy describes our website data practices in good faith. It is not a substitute
        for the HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices that governs Protected Health Information collected
        during your patient relationship with the clinic. For legal advice on your specific situation,
        consult an attorney.
      </em>
    </p>
  </SectionContainer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .updated { color: var(--color-mute); margin: 0; font-size: var(--text-sm); }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-ink-strong);
  }
  ul {
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
  hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }
  .disclaimer {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    background: var(--color-paper-tint);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }
</style>
